tactic used to proxy traffic in or out of a network, using the beacon as the pivot point

SOCKS (socket secure) proxy:
  to start the proxy via beacon:
    beacon> socks 1080
  to connect on Windows using proxifier:
    create a new proxy server profile, Profile > Proxy Servers
    enter the IP of the team server and the port (e.g. 1080)
    select the corresponding "SOCKS" protocol
    we can then add a proxification rule to specify the IP (range) of our target host
  to authenticate on windows (on attacker windows desktop):
    authenticate using kerberos tickets (NOTE: add the hostname first, PS C:\Users\Attacker> Add-Content -Path C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts -Value '10.10.120.1 lon-dc-1')
    then create a credential object:
      PS C:\Users\Attacker> $Cred = Get-Credential CONTOSO.COM\rsteel
      PS C:\Users\Attacker> Get-ADUser -Filter 'ServicePrincipalName -like "*"' -Credential $Cred -Server lon-dc-1

